    • Method Detail

      • withRows

        default THIS withRows(int rows)
        Sets the number of rows in the selects. If the number of rows is set to 0 or less, the actual number of displayed rows is determined implicitly by the selects.

        If a height if set (using Sizeable.setHeight(String) or Sizeable.setHeight(float, Unit)) it overrides the number of rows. Leave the height undefined to use this method.

        Parameters:
        rows - the number of rows to set.
        Returns:
        this (for method chaining)
        See Also:
        TwinColSelect.setRows(int)
